
test_misaligned: Test that exceptions due to misalined accesses
                 are handled correctly

Usage: cmtest cmd -f100 [options] [parameters]

The permitted options and their corresponding parameters are listed below:

buffer:
        set [byte array 0 ... 7]
        reset
asm:
    load word:
        lw [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)]
    load word compressed:
        lw_c [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)]
    load word via sp:
        lwsp [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)]
    load half word:
        lh [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)]
    load unsigned half word:
        lhu [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)]
    store word:
        sw [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)] [word to store]
    store word compressed:
        sw_c [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)] [word to store]
    store word via sp:
        swsp [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)] [word to store]
    store half word:
        sh [offset 0 to 4] [offset sign 0 (-) to 1 (+)] [half word to store]
mem:
    copy data between buffers:
        copy [offset 0 to 1] [offset 0 to 1] [loops 0 to 10000]

Note: all assembly operations are performed on a 64 bits buffer and
      all offset values are referred to the beginning of the buffer.

Load the user container and see usage in logs:

$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_misaligned.img
$ cmtest log

Reset the buffer:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 buffer reset
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 8 bytes OK
00000000: 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00                           |........|

Set the buffer:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 buffer set %0001020304050607
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 8 bytes OK
00000000: 00 01 02 03 04 05 06 07                           |........|

Load the first word with positive offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm lw 0 1
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: 00 01 02 03                                       |....|

Load the second word with negative offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm lw 4 0
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: 04 05 06 07                                       |....|

Load an unaligned word with negative offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm lw 1 0
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: 01 02 03 04                                       |....|

Store a word with positive offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm sw 0 1 0xffffffff
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: ff ff ff ff                                       |....|

Store a word with negative offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm sw 0 0 0xffffffff
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: ff ff ff ff                                       |....|

Store a word within unaligned address with positive offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm sw 2 1 0xffffffff
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: ff ff ff ff                                       |....|

Load a signed half-word with positive offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm lh 0 1
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: ff ff ff ff                                       |....|

Load a unsigned half-word with positive offset:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 asm lh 0 1
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: ff ff ff ff                                       |....|

Perform 100 32-bits copies between buffers and
obtain the elapsed time:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 mem copy 0 0 100
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 8 bytes OK
00000000: 8a fc 08 00 00 00 00 00                           |........|

Perform 100 32 bits copies between buffers (with aligned
and unaligned address) and obtain the elapsed time:

$ cmtest cmd -f100 mem copy 0 1 100
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 8 bytes OK
00000000: 8a d8 0d 00 00 00 00 00                           |........|

Unload the user container:

$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
